I"2<ol>
  <li>Bring a pot of water to the boil and add the Salt. Once boiled add the Spaghetti and cook as per directions.</li>
  <li>Heat the oil in a man and fry off the Bacon. Add the Garlic to the pan and once fragrant, add the Mushrooms. Once the Mushrooms are softened add the Paprika and cook for a minute. Deglaze the pan with the White Wine and stir the mixture.</li>
  <li>Over a low heat add the mixture and cream to the cooked pasta. Then add the Eggs and Cheese stirring through.</li>
  <li>Serve with Garlic Bread and garnish with Parsley.</li>
</ol>
